<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  Template for the future SMAppService-registered agent (see
  RegisterAgent.swift in this directory). NOT wired into the current shell/
  build -- "Start at Login" uses tauri-plugin-autostart's plain
  ~/Library/LaunchAgents plist today (see shell/src-tauri/src/main.rs).

  To actually use this, a future build step would need to:
    1. Copy this file to
       PersonalDB.app/Contents/Library/LaunchAgents/com.personal_db.daemon.plist
       (SMAppService.agent(plistName:) requires it at exactly that path
       inside the signed bundle -- it will not find it anywhere else).
    2. Make sure the path in BundleProgram below matches wherever the
       frozen daemon sidecar (packaging/freeze-daemon.sh's
       personal-db-daemon-aarch64-apple-darwin launcher, plus its sibling
       python/ tree) actually lands once shell/'s tauri.conf.json grows a
       bundle.externalBin + bundle.resources entry for it. The path below
       is a *guess* at Tauri's externalBin convention
       (Contents/MacOS/<name>-<target-triple>) -- verify against the real
       built bundle layout before relying on it.
    3. Re-sign the app afterward (this plist lives inside the signed
       bundle, so it's covered by the outer `codesign` in
       sign-and-notarize.sh -- no separate signing step needed for the
       plist itself, but changing it after signing invalidates the
       signature like any other bundle content change).

  BundleProgram (not Program/ProgramArguments with an absolute path) is
  deliberate: SMAppService-managed plists are resolved relative to the
  app bundle, which is what makes this survive the user installing the
  .app anywhere (Applications, Downloads, a different volume) -- the
  plain-plist LaunchAgent approach tauri-plugin-autostart uses today has
  to bake in an absolute path instead, which is the other half of the
  fragility this replaces.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>Label</key>
    <string>com.personal_db.daemon</string>

    <key>BundleProgram</key>
    <string>Contents/MacOS/personal-db-daemon-aarch64-apple-darwin</string>

    <key>ProgramArguments</key>
    <array>
        <string>dev</string>
        <string>daemon</string>
        <string>run</string>
    </array>

    <key>RunAtLoad</key>
    <true/>

    <!-- Restart on crash, but not in a tight loop if it's failing fast --
         SuccessfulExit=false means "only restart if it exited nonzero or
         was killed", not "restart unconditionally"; ThrottleInterval
         caps the restart rate. -->
    <key>KeepAlive</key>
    <dict>
        <key>SuccessfulExit</key>
        <false/>
    </dict>
    <key>ThrottleInterval</key>
    <integer>10</integer>

    <key>StandardOutPath</key>
    <string>~/Library/Logs/PersonalDB/daemon.log</string>
    <key>StandardErrorPath</key>
    <string>~/Library/Logs/PersonalDB/daemon.err.log</string>

    <!-- PERSONAL_DB_ROOT intentionally left unset here -- the daemon's own
         default (~/personal_db) matches what the CLI and this Tauri shell
         both resolve to when the env var is absent, so there's no need to
         hardcode it in the launchd environment. -->
</dict>
</plist>
